Under current statute Governor of Oklahoma may grant a commutation of the death sentence, but must have the Recommendation of Clemency From a Board or Advisory Group. The only post-Furman pardon was granted by Gov. Brad Henry on May 13 , 2004 to Osvaldo Torres
